# Application Icons

This directory contains the application icons for {{ project_name }}.

## Required Icons

Tauri requires the following icon files:

- `32x32.png` - 32x32 PNG (Windows taskbar)
- `128x128.png` - 128x128 PNG (macOS dock, Windows Alt+Tab)
- `128x128@2x.png` - 256x256 PNG (Retina displays)
- `icon.icns` - macOS icon bundle
- `icon.ico` - Windows icon
- `icon.png` - 512x512 PNG (source image)

## Generating Icons

You can automatically generate all required icons from a single 512x512 PNG source image:

```bash
cd src-tauri
pnpm tauri icon path/to/your-icon.png
```

This will generate all required icon formats.

## Icon Guidelines

### Design Requirements

1. **Size**: Start with a 1024x1024 or 512x512 PNG
2. **Format**: PNG with transparent background
3. **Shape**: Square with rounded corners optional
4. **Padding**: Include ~10% padding from edges
5. **Colors**: Use brand colors, ensure good contrast

### Platform Considerations

**macOS:**
- Use transparent background
- Include subtle shadows
- Follow [macOS icon guidelines](https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/app-icons)

**Windows:**
- Can use transparent or solid background
- Include multiple sizes in .ico
- Follow [Windows icon guidelines](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/apps/design/style/iconography/app-icon-design)

**Linux:**
- Transparent background preferred
- Simple, clear design
- Follow [freedesktop.org icon theme spec](https://specifications.freedesktop.org/icon-theme-spec/icon-theme-spec-latest.html)

### Testing Your Icons

After generating icons:

1. Build the app: `pnpm build`
2. Check the icon in:
   - macOS: Finder, Dock, Alt+Tab
   - Windows: Explorer, Taskbar, Alt+Tab
   - Linux: File manager, application launcher

### Color Recommendations

- Use 2-3 main colors maximum
- Ensure icon is recognizable at 32x32
- Test on both light and dark backgrounds
- Avoid fine details that won't scale well

## Example Icon Generation

```bash
# 1. Create your 512x512 icon (icon.png)
# 2. Navigate to src-tauri directory
cd src-tauri

# 3. Generate all icon formats
pnpm tauri icon icons/icon.png

# 4. Icons will be generated in the icons/ directory
```

## Manual Icon Creation

If you prefer to create icons manually:

**macOS (.icns):**
```bash
# Use Image2Icon or iconutil
mkdir icon.iconset
sips -z 16 16     icon.png --out icon.iconset/icon_16x16.png
sips -z 32 32     icon.png --out icon.iconset/icon_16x16@2x.png
# ... repeat for all sizes
iconutil -c icns icon.iconset
```

**Windows (.ico):**
Use tools like:
- [IcoFX](https://icofx.ro/)
- [GIMP](https://www.gimp.org/)
- [ImageMagick](https://imagemagick.org/)

```bash
convert icon.png -define icon:auto-resize=256,128,64,48,32,16 icon.ico
```

